# Server-Only Data Access

All data retrieval and all database mutations (insert, update, delete) **must** happen on the server. Never access the database from client components.

## Data Retriever

Use **React Server Components** (RSC) for all data reads. Pass data down as props to Client Components.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — data retriever in a Server Component
// app/decks/page.tsx  (no "use client")
import { db } from "@/lib/db";
import { decks } from "@/lib/schema";
import { eq } from "drizzle-orm";
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";

export default async function DecksPage() {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  const userDecks = await db.select().from(decks).where(eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId!));
  return <DeckList decks={userDecks} />;
}

// ❌ BAD — data retriever in a Client Component
"use client";
useEffect(() => {
  fetch("/api/decks").then(...); // avoid unnecessary round-trips
}, []);
```

## Mutations (Insert / Update / Delete)

Use **Server Actions** for all writes. Never call Drizzle from a Client Component.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — Server Action
// app/decks/actions.ts
"use server";
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";
import { db } from "@/lib/db";
import { decks } from "@/lib/schema";

export async function createDeck(title: string) {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthorized");
  await db.insert(decks).values({ title, clerkUserId: userId });
}

// ❌ BAD — mutation from a Client Component
"use client";
import { db } from "@/lib/db"; // never import db in client code
await db.insert(decks).values({ ... });
```

## Rules

- Server Components: data retriever only (no `useState`, no `useEffect`)
- Server Actions (`"use server"`): all inserts, updates, and deletes
- Client Components (`"use client"`): UI interaction only — receive data via props or Server Action results
- Never import `db` or `schema` from client-side code
